From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 13:02:40 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 8: chapter kinds
 (foundation/replace/extend/glue/gate/verify)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three changes that hang together:

1. Storyboard cards lose the description paragraph. The card
   was already small and the title plus footer carry enough
   per-card information; the detail rail on the right shows
   the full summary, bullets, and connections when a card is
   clicked. Card height drops from 156px to 96px.

2. Card colours mean something. Top stripe (and a small mono
   kind badge in the head) now reflects the chapter's semantic
   role:
     foundation - blue   - introduces a primitive others build on
     replace    - red    - rewrites existing behaviour
     extend     - green  - extends a foundation primitive
     glue       - grey   - wiring / plumbing that connects others
     gate       - yellow - config / feature flag controlling activation
     verify     - purple - tests / observability / docs
   Same six-kind palette the design demo uses. Replaces the
   previous tier-depth palette, which carried no semantic
   meaning beyond 'how deep in the dependency graph'.

3. Stronger prompt for kind + edge labelling. The model was
   under-tagging gates/verifies. The system prompt now:
     - explicitly defines the 6 chapter kinds and tells the
       model to prefer kind=verify for any test-heavy chapter,
       kind=gate for any config-heavy chapter
     - tells the model to be aggressive about emitting
       'verifies' edges from test chapters to the units they
       exercise (one edge per unit, not one combined 'depends')
     - tells the model to be aggressive about emitting 'gates'
       edges from config chapters to chapters whose behaviour
       the flag controls
   Parser falls back to a path-based heuristic when the model
   omits kind: predominantly *_test.* / *.spec.* / tests/ →
   verify; predominantly *.yaml / *.toml / *.env / helm/ →
   gate; otherwise glue.

Cache version bumps from v2 to v3; old caches are dropped on
read so the next tour open re-generates with the new shape.
